1. Step - Install/Update kubectl CLI to the latest version:
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl/#install-kubectl-binary-with-curl-on-linux

If this is not done, you will get the following error message:
error: SchemaError(io.k8s.api.autoscaling.v2beta2.HorizontalPodAutoscalerList): invalid object doesn't have additional properties

2. Step - Launch EKS cluster with Kubernetes version 1.14:
aws eks create-cluster --kubernetes-version 1.14 --name eksworkshop-cf --role-arn "${SERVICE_ROLE}" --resources-vpc-config subnetIds="${SUBNET_IDS}",securityGroupIds="${SECURITY_GROUP}"

3. Step - Create kubeconfig file:
https://eksworkshop.com/cloudformation/kubeconfig.html

4. Step - Add worker nodes:
export SUBNET_IDS=$(aws cloudformation describe-stacks --stack-name "eksworkshop-cf" --query "Stacks[0].Outputs[?OutputKey=='SubnetIds'].OutputValue" --output text)
export SECURITY_GROUP=$(aws cloudformation describe-stacks --stack-name "eksworkshop-cf" --query "Stacks[0].Outputs[?OutputKey=='SecurityGroups'].OutputValue" --output text)
export VPC_ID=$(aws cloudformation describe-stacks --stack-name "eksworkshop-cf" --query "Stacks[0].Outputs[?OutputKey=='VpcId'].OutputValue" --output text)

aws cloudformation create-stack --stack-name "eksworkshop-cf-worker-nodes" \
--template-url "https://amazon-eks.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/1.10.3/2018-06-05/amazon-eks-nodegroup.yaml" \
--capabilities CAPABILITY_IAM \
--parameters \
ParameterKey=KeyName,ParameterValue=eksworkshop \
ParameterKey=NodeImageId,ParameterValue=ami-038a987c6425a84ad \
ParameterKey=NodeGroupName,ParameterValue=eks-howto-workers \
ParameterKey=ClusterControlPlaneSecurityGroup,ParameterValue=$SECURITY_GROUP \
ParameterKey=VpcId,ParameterValue=$VPC_ID \
ParameterKey=Subnets,ParameterValue=\"$SUBNET_IDS\" \
ParameterKey=ClusterName,ParameterValue=eksworkshop-cf

--> Use AMI ami-038a987c6425a84ad! Refer to the following link: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/eks-optimized-ami.html

5. Step - Create and add configmap:
Please follow the steps of chapter "To enable worker nodes to join your cluster" under https://docs.aws.amazon.com/eks/latest/userguide/launch-workers.html

6. Step - Check worker nodes status:
kubectl get nodes --watch

Please note: It take some seconds until the worker nodes are ready!
